This paper deals with game theory and mechanism design, specifically in the context of auctions. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the efficiency and revenue of auctions, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study of auctions is a classic topic in computer science and economics, falling under the sub-category of computational social choice (cs.EC). The paper also uses mathematical techniques to analyze the equilibria, which could fall under the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or machine learning (cs.LG).
